WELL now not only am I a secret shopper (it's when you go to a store and buy shit and then write the company and tell them how good or shitty the store did then get PAID) now I also sell Avon. So if you need Avon shit order through me. If your not even in Maryland well for 3 bucks they deliver it to your door. And yes Avon is a worldwide thing. 

Kaden rolls over now! Well he doesn't do it all the time, but he did it for the second time in two weeks today. He also slept alot today I think he's exhausted. We spent most of the week outside my house because we didn't have AC. Well we FINALLY have it and he SLEEPS ALL DAY! I didn't get a chance to talk to him today. Usually we talk for about 2 hours everyday. Well I talk he just babbles back and smiles really big. When he starts talking I'm in so much troubgle. The amount oof babbling that he does right now tells me I'm gonna have one of those "Why?" kids. I'm actually looking forward to it.

And he's 3 1/2 months old and he's eyes keep changing color. Monday they were this awesome green color. Tuesday they were gray. Wednesday they were hazel, thrusday they were brown, and today they were this golden brown color and last time he was awake there was a definite green tint to them. He's growing up to fast and I'm glad I'm not missing it. I'd hate to put him in daycare, and recently due to horror stories about daycare I don't think I ever want to.

Don't know what I'm talking about? Google Kaleb Schwade. Then tell me I'm not doing the right thing. Wanna help me out? Order some Avon even if it's for your mom, your ex, that chick you met at the club last week. The more money I make the less chance I have of having to put him in a daycare where he can get sick hurt or worse. Wanna see Kaden in all his glory? Email me there's tons of pics.

A little girl walked into my store with her dad today to do some school shopping. He said he had no idea what to get her and kinda handed her over to me and sat in one of our visitor chairs. So after asking her name and age, we weighed her and started picking out clothes to try on. $378 and are 17 outfits later we have pity on Daddy and call it a day. As we're ringing her up he asks her if this is what she wanted and if she got everthing. She brings up needing to get shoes (aside from the 3 pairs she's got from us) and a bra (oh poor Daddy) she's happy. 

I really love my job.
